trans-unit.source: Patterns are used to match values against structures and to, optionally, bind variables to values inside these structures. They are also used in variable declarations and parameters for functions and closures.
trans-unit.target: 模式用于将值与结构进行匹配,并选择性地将变量与这些结构中的值进行绑定。它们还用于变量声明和函数及闭包的参数中。

trans-unit.source: Patterns can be used to destructurestructs, enums, and tuples. Destructuring breaks up a value into its component pieces. The syntax used is almost the same as when creating such values. In a pattern whose scrutinee expression has a struct, enum or tuple type, a placeholder (_) stands in for a single data field, whereas a wildcard .. stands in for all the remaining fields of a particular variant. When destructuring a data structure with named (but not numbered) fields, it is allowed to write fieldname as a shorthand for fieldname: fieldname.
trans-unit.target: 模式可用于解构结构，枚举和元组。重组将价值分解成各个组成部分。使用的语法与创建此类值时几乎相同。在其一个图案scrutinee表达具有 struct ， enum 或 tuple 类型，占位符（ _ ）代表在用于单个数据字段，而一个通配符 .. 代表在所有特定变体的剩余字段。在使用命名（但未编号）字段对数据结构进行销毁时，可以写入 fieldname 作为 fieldname: fieldname 的简写：fieldname。

trans-unit.source: Patterns come in two forms: refutable and irrefutable. Patterns that will match for any possible value passed are irrefutable. An example would be x in the statement let x = 5; because x matches anything and therefore cannot fail to match. Patterns that can fail to match for some possible value are refutable. An example would be Some(x) in the expression if let Some(x) = a_value because if the value in the a_value variable is None rather than Some, the Some(x) pattern will not match.
trans-unit.target: 模式有两种形式：可辩驳和不可辩驳。与传递的任何可能值匹配的模式是不可辩驳的。一个示例是语句中的 x ， let x = 5; 因为 x 匹配任何东西，因此不能不匹配。可能无法匹配某些可能值的模式是可更改的。 if let Some(x) = a_value ，则表达式中的 Some(x) 就是一个例子，因为如果 a_value 变量中的值为 None 而不是 Some ，则 Some(x) 模式将不匹配。

trans-unit.source: Procedural Macros for Generating Code from Attributes
trans-unit.target: 从属性生成代码的程序化宏。

trans-unit.source: Procedural macro crates almost always will link to the compiler-provided proc_macro crate. The proc_macro crate provides types required for writing procedural macros and facilities to make it easier.
trans-unit.target: 程序宏板条箱几乎总是链接到编译器提供的 proc_macro crate。该 proc_macro 箱为编写程序宏和设施，以方便需要的类型。

trans-unit.source: Procedural macros allow you to run code at compile time that operates over Rust syntax, both consuming and producing Rust syntax. You can sort of think of procedural macros as functions from an AST to another AST.
trans-unit.target: 程序性宏允许你在编译时运行在Rust语法上操作的代码,既消耗又产生Rust语法。你可以把程序性宏看作是一个AST到另一个AST的函数。

trans-unit.source: Procedural macros are unhygienic. This means they behave as if the output token stream was simply written inline to the code it's next to. This means that it's affected by external items and also affects external imports.
trans-unit.target: 程序宏是不卫生的。这意味着它们的行为就像是将输出令牌流简单地内联地写入与其旁边的代码一样。这意味着它受外部物品的影响，也影响外部进口。

trans-unit.source: Procedural macros have two ways of reporting errors. The first is to panic. The second is to emit a compile_error macro invocation.
trans-unit.target: 程序宏有两种报告错误的方法。首先是恐慌。第二个是发出 compile_error 宏调用。

trans-unit.source: Procedural macros must be defined in a crate with the crate type of proc-macro.
trans-unit.target: 程序宏必须在带有 proc-macro 的板条箱类型的板条箱中定义。

trans-unit.source: Procedural macros run during compilation, and thus have the same resources that the compiler has. For example, standard input, error, and output are the same that the compiler has access to. Similarly, file access is the same. Because of this, procedural macros have the same security concerns that Cargo's build scripts have.
trans-unit.target: 程序宏在编译期间运行，因此具有与编译器相同的资源。例如，标准输入，错误和输出与编译器可以访问的相同。同样，文件访问是相同的。因此，过程宏与Cargo的构建脚本具有相同的安全问题。
